                                                              <<center>>=== //**__Summary__**// ===<</center>>
<<center>><<size 125%>>You may be asking yourself: \\<<color blue>>"Do I want this plugin...? I mean would it really be that easy??"<</color>>\\Yes. And yes it is.\\<<color gray>>.. totally going to be...<</color>><</size>><</center>>
MCHungerGames is designed to make running Hunger Games-style events much easier. Sure, there are some nice servers and plugins that have achieved this, but they constantly require Moderators/Admins to be on, and paying attention.
\\If you don't know what Hunger Games is look [[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hunger_Games|here]] for the series by Suzanne Collins, and [[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hunger_Games_universe#The_Hunger_Games|here]] for the namesake fictional "Hunger Games" event
\\<<color white>>.<</color>>\\
=== **++Things I wish to add++** ===
* Reaping that selects from players that have played for an X to Y amount of hours
* Maybe a hook into factions (so admins could set up "districts")? Depending on what the most popular faction plugin is
** Also depending on this, but may hook into economy plugin too. (ie. Give rewards to the winning "district") 
**Either:**
* Script-able game events (eg. Fires, Floods, Poison Gas)
* **OR** API for custom events
